title: PMQs: Corbyn and Cameron on tax credits
text:
Media playback is unsupported on your device PMQs: Corbyn and Cameron on tax credits 21 October 2015 Last updated at 13:51 BST
Labour leader Jeremy Corbyn questions the prime minister on tax credits, highlighting Conservative divisions over the policy.
David Cameron said the changes are part of a package including a higher living wage and tax reductions, and that he was "delighted" the measure was approved by MPs in Tuesday's vote.
PMQs in text and video updates on BBC Politics Live
